						               													<description>This is a promotional game for &amp;quot;Lintsi&amp;quot;, ie. Linnanm&amp;auml;ki, the main amusement park of Helsinki since 1950. In this vaguely Monopoly-like roll-and-move game, the players first need to divide the various rides and attractions between themselves, using their starting cash in a small sub-game. The main game includes touring Linnanm&amp;auml;ki for a pre-agreed number of rounds for each player (a minimum of five is recommended), collecting cash when passing Go, taking event cards as instructed, and visiting the various attractions and paying for a ticket to their owners - or possibly even buying the attraction from the bank if the previous owner already went bankrupt and is out of the game, and the attraction has thus become available in the open market again. The player with the most wealth in all collected assets - cash and attractions - at the end of the game wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Based on the Linnanm&amp;auml;ki attractions included, the game is probably from 1975 at the latest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
